properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 8 at 3:03AM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Accumulating Snow Late Tonight and Sunday...

.A fast moving storm system will bring a round of snow to the
area late tonight and Sunday.

Snow will begin developing after midnight and rapidly increase in
areal coverage as the storm system arrives. Warm air flowing north
is expected to change the snow into a rain/snow mix Sunday
afternoon with a period of freezing rain or sleet possible.

Drier air moving in aloft will shut down the heavier precipitation
during the afternoon but drizzle or freezing drizzle may still be
possible.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4
inches.

* WHERE...In Iowa, Buchanan, Delaware and Dubuque Counties. In
Illinois, Jo Daviess and Stephenson Counties.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 6 PM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and reduced
visibilities.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snowfall rates at times may approach an
inch per hour between 6 and 10 AM Sunday.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

In Illinois, go to www.gettingaroundillinois.com for road
conditions.
In Iowa, call 511 for road conditions.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 6 PM CST SUNDAY
